      "message": "As the code stands right now _fetchTasks won\u0027t be called when filterByUser is changed. Since you are storing the value of the property in an attribute you can use the attributeChangedCallback to add that functionality.\n\n  static get observedAttributes() {\n    return [\u0027filter_by_user\u0027];\n  }\n\n\n  attributeChangedCallback(name, oldValue, newValue) {\n    switch (name) {\n      case \u0027filter_by_user\u0027:\n        if (newValue !\u003d\u003d \u0027\u0027) {\n          this._fetchTasks(); \n        }\n        break;\n    }\n  }",
